Description: You are looking at a magnificent Ebony (Satin) Moon Rising Nitrocellulose Lacquer finished 2003 Gibson ES-339 Studio that sizzles with pure tone. It can effortlessly switch between smooth as butter or down and dirty grit. 100% original with great feel and playability. From the creators of this MADE IN AMERICA masterwork ax: "Close to the size of a Les Paul, this affordable model features the same great-sounding '57 Classic (neck) and Super '57 Classic (bridge) pickups and semi-hollowbody design of its siblings minus the binding and block inlays. It comes with simplified controls, soft C profile playing, redesigned neck dimensions, an improved truss rod system, rolled neck binding, low profile frets, Grover tuners and locking stopbar tailpiece. Includes hardshell case." Some of the features of this cool guitar include: * Model: ES-339 Studio Memphis * Color: Black Satin, high gloss nitro lacquer * Body Style: Double cut-away, semi-hollow w dual f-holes * Top & Back: Maple, 3-ply * Center Block: Maple * Neck: 1-piece maple, set neck * Fretboard: Torrified maple, 12” radius, 22 frets * Fret Inlays: Pearloid dots * Nut: Black corian, 1.6875” width * Scale Length: 24-3/4" * Binding: Black, top, back and fretboard * Pickups: Gibson 57 classic & super 57 humbuckers * Neck Profile: Soft C, 1st fret .805”, 12th fret .885" * Bridge: ABR-1 style, adjustable with stopper * Hardware: Nickel * Tuners: Grover rotomatic, nickel * Controls: 2 volume & 2 tone, 3-way toggle switch * Knobs: Black top hats * Weight: 7 lbs. * Serial # 10417xxx
Title: Gibson ES-339 Studio Memphis in Ebony (Satin) Moon Rising 2003 w/OHSC (0056)
ConditionDescription: Excellent condition cosmetically and mint playing condition. One minor ding on back of body and minor ding on side of headstock. See pictures.
